<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Trace Report — {{ investigation_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
<style>
  /* Trace-report-specific overrides — internal forensic
     worksheet aesthetic. Lighter on chrome, more density
     than the customer-facing freeze letter. */
  .internal-stamp {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: 0.6em;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--confidential);
    color: var(--confidential);
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  .stat-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 0.4em 1.2em;
    margin: var(--space-md) 0 var(--space-lg);
    padding: 0.8em 1em;
    background: var(--paper-tint);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--gold-accent);
  }
  .stat-grid > div {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-size: var(--type-small);
  }
  .stat-grid dt { color: var(--ink-quiet); font-weight: 500; }
  .stat-grid dd { font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink); margin: 0; }
  .freeze-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 1px 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .freeze-badge.high   { background: #DCFCE7; color: #14532D; }
  .freeze-badge.medium { background: #FEF3C7; color: #5C2D0F; }
  .freeze-badge.low    { background: #FED7AA; color: #5C1F09; }
  .freeze-badge.none   { background: #F1F5F9; color: #475569; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Internal Use Only</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Forensic Worksheet · Wallet Trace Report</div>
    <h1>Trace Report
      <span class="internal-stamp">Internal Use Only</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Data-only summary of on-chain trace findings.
      {% if label %}Label: <strong>{{ label }}</strong>.{% endif %}
      Not for external distribution — this artifact contains raw
      investigative data without the case narrative or
      customer-facing prose. For an externally-shareable summary,
      see the freeze-request and LE-handoff deliverables.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Investigation ID</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ investigation_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Traced Wallet</dt>
      <dd><a class="mono" href="{{ wallet_explorer_url }}">{{ wallet_address }}</a></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Chain</dt>
      <dd>{{ chain }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Run Timestamp</dt>
      <dd>{{ generated_at }} UTC</dd>
    </div>
    {% if label %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Label</dt>
      <dd>{{ label }}</dd>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  </dl>
</section>

<h2>1. Trace Summary</h2>
<dl class="stat-grid">
  <div><dt>Total transfers analyzed</dt><dd>{{ stats.total_transfers }}</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Max depth reached</dt><dd>{{ stats.max_depth_reached }}</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Total flow value (USD)</dt><dd>{{ stats.total_flow_usd }}</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Destinations identified</dt><dd>{{ stats.destinations_count }}</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Trace started</dt><dd class="mono">{{ stats.trace_started_at }}</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Trace completed</dt><dd class="mono">{{ stats.trace_completed_at }}</dd></div>
</dl>

<h2>2. Destination Addresses</h2>
{% if destinations %}
<p class="small">
  Every distinct destination wallet identified by the trace, with
  current holdings priced at fetch time. Click any address to open
  it on the chain explorer.
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Address</th>
      <th>Role / Label</th>
      <th>Asset</th>
      <th>Balance</th>
      <th>USD Value</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for d in destinations %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono"><a href="{{ d.explorer_url }}">{{ d.address_short }}</a></td>
      <td>{{ d.role }}{% if d.label %}<br/><span class="small secondary">{{ d.label }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td>{{ d.symbol or '—' }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ d.balance_human or '—' }}</td>
      <td class="amount">{{ d.usd_value_human or '—' }}</td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% else %}
<p>No destination addresses identified beyond the seed wallet.</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>3. Freeze Potential</h2>
{% if freezable_rows %}
<p class="small">
  Destinations holding assets the issuer can freeze. Capability
  taxonomy: <strong>HIGH</strong> (issuer has direct freeze
  authority), <strong>MEDIUM</strong> (issuer can freeze with some
  friction), <strong>LOW</strong> (technically possible but
  unprecedented or contested), <strong>NOT FREEZABLE</strong>
  (staking/permissionless contract — issuer has no power).
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Address</th>
      <th>Asset</th>
      <th>Balance</th>
      <th>USD Value</th>
      <th>Issuer</th>
      <th>Freezability</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for f in freezable_rows %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono"><a href="{{ f.explorer_url }}">{{ f.address_short }}</a></td>
      <td>{{ f.symbol }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ f.amount }}</td>
      <td class="amount">{{ f.usd }}</td>
      <td>{{ f.issuer }}</td>
      <td>
        <span class="freeze-badge {{ f.capability_class }}">
          {{ f.capability }}
        </span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% else %}
<p>No destinations identified holding freezable assets. The
trace's terminal wallets either hold non-freezable assets (native
gas tokens, non-stablecoin tokens with no issuer-level controls)
or are at exchanges / mixers / bridges that require a different
recovery path (subpoena, mixer report, bridge operator
notification).</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>4. Flow Visualization</h2>
{% if flow_filename %}
<p class="attachment-note">
  The complete fund-flow diagram is provided as a separate SVG
  attachment (<span class="mono">{{ flow_filename }}</span>)
  accompanying this report. Open in any modern browser to inspect
  at full resolution; each wallet node links directly to its
  on-chain explorer record.
</p>
{% else %}
<p>Flow diagram unavailable for this trace.</p>
{% endif %}

<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>{{ investigation_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Internal Use Only.</span>
    Not for distribution to issuers, exchanges, or law enforcement.
    For external-shareable artifacts see freeze_request_*.html and
    le_handoff_*.html in the same investigation folder.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
